385		// Implement memory mapped register select and write logic generation
386		// The write data is accepted and written to memory mapped registers when
387		// axi_awready, S_AXI_WVALID, axi_wready and S_AXI_WVALID are asserted. Write strobes are used to
388		// select byte enables of slave registers while writing.
389		// These registers are cleared when reset (active low) is applied.
390		// Slave register write enable is asserted when valid address and data are available
391		// and the slave is ready to accept the write address and write data.
392		assign slv_reg_wren = axi_wready && S_AXI_WVALID && axi_awready && S_AXI_AWVALID;
